JOHANNESBURG A newborn baby girl was found dead in a dustbin outside a small shopping centre in Kelvin, Woodmead in Johannesburg on Sunday morning, paramedics said.READ: Child stabbed to death at German refugee shelterShortly after 10 am, paramedics from ER24 arrived on the scene where they found the baby in the dustbin. She was still wrapped in a small blanket, ER24 spokesman Werner Vermaak said. It is understood that a man was going through the dustbin when he made the discovery. He called the security guards at the shopping centre which in turn alerted ER24 and the police. Sadly, there was nothing that paramedics could do for the little girl. It appeared as if she had been dumped during the early hours of the morning. She was later declared dead by paramedics. The police attended the scene and will investigate, Vermaak said.African News Agency